The food delivery giant now forecasts orders on apps will rise by between four and 12 percent this year, down from its 15 to 25 percent target. UK and Ireland sales growth fell from 12 to four percent since the start of 2022. Susannah Streeter, senior investment and markets analyst at Hargreaves Lansdown, said: "Expensive takeaways are likely to be among the first treats to fall by the wayside as households grapple with soaring bills especially as higher costs are feeding through to pricier menus." Deliveroo's shares have more than halved this year.